The problem is about constructing a cube with volume X times a given cube using compass and straightedge, which is equivalent to constructing the cube root of X. A length is constructible only if it involves only square roots, so cube roots are generally not constructible unless X is a perfect cube. Among the set {3, 17, 8, 27, 343, 1331}, the perfect cubes are 8, 27, 343, and 1331, so only those are constructible.

Thus the correct answer list is [0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1], which corresponds to option C.

